    title: 'Gestalt Laws',
    def: 'The umbrella term for the full family of Gestalt perception principles — Proximity, Similarity, Closure, Continuation, Figure/Ground, Common Region, and Prägnanz — describing how humans perceive visual elements as organized wholes rather than isolated parts.',
