    title: 'Cognitive Psychology',
    def: 'The branch of psychology studying internal mental processes — perception, memory, attention, reasoning, language — that underlies nearly every UX law and heuristic used in design.',
    why: 'Cognitive psychology is the scientific foundation beneath the entire vocabulary of UX laws and heuristics — understanding it as a discipline, not just memorizing individual named effects, helps a designer reason about NEW situations that don\'t map neatly to any single named law.',
