    examples: [
      { label: 'Example · Glanceable, context-aware wearable design', text: 'A candidate designing a fitness-tracking wearable interface prioritized a single, large, glanceable metric (current heart rate zone) over a dense dashboard, explicitly reasoning that users would view it during active movement with only a brief glance available.' },
      { label: 'Example · A shrunk mobile design mistaken for wearable design', text: 'A candidate\'s wearable design was essentially their mobile design shrunk to fit a smaller screen, with the same information density — missing the fundamentally different glanceable, context-of-use considerations this prompt specifically tests.' },
    ],
    mistake: 'Designing for a wearable device by simply shrinking a mobile design\'s information density, rather than fundamentally rethinking for glanceable, single-priority information display appropriate to a wearable\'s extreme constraints.',
