    examples: [
      { label: 'Example · Logically grouped, genuinely usable preferences', text: 'A notification settings page grouped options into clear categories (social, product updates, security) with sensible defaults and simple category-level toggles, avoiding an overwhelming flat list of many individual settings.' },
      { label: 'Example · An overwhelming, ungrouped preferences list', text: 'A settings page listed dozens of individual, ungrouped notification toggles with no logical organization, making it genuinely difficult for users to find and adjust the specific setting they wanted.' },
    ],
    mistake: 'Presenting notification preferences as a long, ungrouped flat list of individual toggles — logical categorization with sensible defaults makes granular control genuinely usable rather than overwhelming.',
