    title: 'Conversational Design',
    def: 'The design of dialogue-based interfaces — chatbots, voice assistants, conversational agents — covering turn-taking, tone, error recovery, and how a system should handle ambiguous or off-topic input.',
    why: 'Conversational interfaces lack the persistent visual affordances of graphical UI, so users can\'t see what\'s possible; conversational design must actively guide users toward what the system can actually do.',
    blocks: [
      { t: 'p', text: 'Effective conversational design establishes a consistent persona and tone, gives users discoverable cues about system capabilities early in the interaction, and handles misunderstandings gracefully by asking clarifying questions rather than failing silently or guessing.' },
    ],
