    title: 'AI Content Filtering',
    def: 'Automated screening of AI-generated or user-submitted content against policy or safety rules before it\'s shown to a user — a distinct layer from moderation of user-generated content.',
    why: 'AI generation systems need their own output filtered, separate from user-generated content moderation, since a model can generate policy-violating content even from an entirely innocuous prompt.',
